title: Puma isn’t included because I haven’t tried it. I run 200K a week, so I go through a lot of running shoes. Here’s my honest ranking based on performance: 1️⃣ Nike – Best super shoe (Alphafly 3), great daily trainers, and exciting new releases. 2️⃣ ASICS – Consistently strong across race, training, and easy runs.
description: Puma isn’t included because I haven’t tried it. I run 200K a week, so I go through a lot of running shoes. Brands love to market their shoes well, but that doesn’t always mean they’re the best. Here’s my honest ranking based on performance: 1️⃣ Nike – Best super shoe (Alphafly 3), great daily trainers, and exciting new releases. 2️⃣ ASICS – Consistently strong across race, training, and easy runs. 3️⃣ HOKA – Top-tier lineup for all types of runs. 4️⃣ Saucony – Some of the best running shoes across the board. 5️⃣ Adidas – Elite race/training shoes, but their easy run options aren’t top-tier. 6️⃣ Diadora – Underrated but solid across daily, training, and racing. 7️⃣ New Balance – Great daily trainers but racing shoes hold them back. 8️⃣ Brooks – Training and racing shoes aren’t quite good enough. 9️⃣ Kiprun – Insane race shoe, solid trainer, weak easy run options. 🔟 ON – Strong race shoe, but lacks depth in the lineup. Other brands like 361 Degrees, Under Armour, Altra, and Mizuno have some solid shoes but not enough across the board. What’s your top running shoe brand? Drop your rankings below! #RunningShoes #MarathonTraining #shoereview

title: Carbon plated running shoes CAN be great but they can so be quite harsh on the feet! Runners should be making decisions on their shoes based on their own strides and preferences. If that means you wear a recovery day shoe for a race then so be it!
description: Carbon plated running shoes CAN be great but they can so be quite harsh on the feet! A lot of newer runners may feel some pressure to get a “race shoe” but the reality is that you can race in almost anything so long as it’s comfortable.  Runners should be making decisions on their shoes based on their own strides and preferences. If that means you wear a recovery day shoe for a race then so be it!  Pick what is more comfortable and what makes you fastest the LAST mile of a race. Not necessarily what’s fastest the first mile!  #creatorsearchinsights #runnerdad #runlifebalance #carbonplatedshoes #runningshoereviews #5amrun #marathonraceshoes #supershoes

description: Rockstarz 🤙🏾 Jump rope or running? 🤔 Let’s break it down: 💪🏾Jump Rope: 	•	Quick  intense full-body workout that boosts your heart rate fast. 	•	Engages your coordination  agility  and spatial awareness. 	•	Burns the same calories in 10 minutes as 30 minutes of jogging! 	•	Great for building bone density and reducing the risk of osteoporosis. 🏃🏽‍♀️Running: 	•	Builds endurance and improves heart health over long distances. 	•	A steady-paced activity that supports weight management. 	•	Done outdoors  it provides vitamin D  which benefits bone health and mood. Which is better? It depends on your goals! If you want a fast  high-intensity workout with tons of versatility  grab your rope. If you love a steady rhythm and outdoor vibes  lace up your running shoes. Better yet—combine both for a balanced routine! Personally  I prefer to jump rope 🪢✨ It’s fun  efficient  and keeps me on my toes (literally!). Oh  and don’t forget—my ongoing jump rope challenge is still happening! Join the challenge and take your fitness to the next level. Let’s crush it together! 💥 #JumpRopeVsRunning #JumpRopeChallenge #FitnessTips #CardioBenefits

And yes, you can still run with a bunion.  ❤️‍🩹 Taping Use KT tape to gently pull the bunion outward, helping to realign the toe and reduce pressure while running Taping tips:  🔸Gently pull big toe away from second toe and tape 🔸Don’t over-pull—it should feel supported but not strained  🔸Avoid over-tightening or restrict
description: As many requested, here’s a video for Running with a Bunion – Taping & Tips.  And yes, you can still run with a bunion.  ❤️‍🩹 Taping Use KT tape to gently pull the bunion outward, helping to realign the toe and reduce pressure while running Taping tips:  🔸Gently pull big toe away from second toe and tape 🔸Don’t over-pull—it should feel supported but not strained  🔸Avoid over-tightening or restricting circulation 🔸Press tape ends firmly to prevent peeling 🔸Stop if pain or irritation occurs   👽Toe spacer I insert a soft toe spacer between big toe and 2nd toe during all distances—even for marathons—for added alignment and comfort. 👟Shoes Choose running shoes with a wide toe box. Men’s models often offer more room than women’s. ASICS Nimbus and Kayano also have wide-fit options. 🦶🏻Insoles Insoles with good arch support to reduce strain on the forefoot and improve overall foot alignment. 🏋🏻‍♀️ Strength  Strength exercises and physiotherapy can help manage symptoms and improve leg & foot strength. ⚠️ Always consult your podiatrist or physiotherapist for advice if you’re dealing with pain or serious injury. #runningtip #bunion #footcare #iloverunning

description: What is the best carbon plated race day shoe for someone that over pronates? DISCLAIMER: This list is not exhaustive and there’s lots of parts of a running trainer that can add stability - I’ve chosen to talk about these as I feel these are some of the most important aspects you should look for in a shoe. Also, I wear neutral shoes, so these recommendations are from my own research rather than my own lived experience - everybody is an individual and what can work for one person does not mean it’ll work for somebody else. … There’s no consensus as to what angle of pronation a person has to have to be considered a pronator - some sources state 15 degrees but there’s nothing definitive out there. I know people who have been suggested to try a stability shoe post gait analysis and instead have worn neutral shoes and they’ve had little to no issue. My favourite phrase - if it’s not broke, don’t fix it. The main reason I’d suggest stability shoes to people is if they develop pain and we are confident that this is related to lack of support in their shoes. @HOKA @Saucony @@adidas  #runtok #Running #marathon

description: I’ve been using these shoes for 2 weeks for my interval and tempo runs. The adizero adios pro 3 is a stable and speedy shoe. It has a highly cushioned midsole that helps with technique. The power return is great and it keeps up with demanding paces.  I have overpronated feet and while the Adios Pro are not specific for overpronation they are wide enough, stable, really comfortable and my feet don’t hurt while running.  I think these shoes are great for quick paces in long distance runs. I will be running the Berlin Marathon with these, I’ll update you soon.  Fun fact: Adidas Adios Pro 3 are the Boston Marathon winner shoes🏆 #Running #marathon #training #shoereview #adidas #adizeroadiospro3

description: How to choose the right running shoe! Share this with someone it might help!  There are typically there types of running shoe conventional, minimalist and maximal Here’s how to choose the right shoe for you. 1️⃣ What type of running? First 5k, trail running or going for a speedy PB on race day. Your shoe will likely suit your goal so a beginners shoe might look different to an advanced runners. 2️⃣ Comfort Does the show feel comfortable on the foot and to walk around it? 3️⃣ Heel to toe drop.  The is the difference in the height of the sole at the heel and forefoot If you are someone that struggles with tight calves and Achilles you might want to avoid shoes with a smaller heel to toe drop.  4️⃣ Fit of the shoe - in particular the toe box! Can your wiggle your big toe in your shoe or do your toes feel cramped making you less efficient when you run? 5️⃣ Cushioning If you are doing longer runs or recovery runs you might want more cushioning and spring in your step 6️⃣ Stability If your foot rolls you might want to opt for a stability shoe over a neutral shoe If you are serious about running, you might want a rotation of shoes. But first and foremost, choose comfort for healthy feet. #runners #Running #ukrunchat #begginnerrunner #runningtips #runningshoes

description: Someone hired me to create visuals for their running brand. No logo. No product shots. Just energy. Why? Because nobody stops for a clean product render. They stop for something they feel. So I didn’t build ads. I built rhythm. Scene by scene, the prompts focused on motion and emotion. Runners at golden hour. Crowds cutting through city streets at night. A lone figure on the track, heat shimmer in the air. Grain in the shadows. Blur at the edge of speed. You can feel the breath, the pavement, the silence. This wasn’t about composition. It was about kinetic memory. What running feels like when you’re not thinking — just moving. These aren’t product visuals. They’re fragments of a world. No floating shoes. No call-to-action buttons. Just story. And sweat. And tension. The product? It lives inside this world — quietly. But the brand? That’s the rhythm. And that’s how you build something that sticks. You don’t promote the product. You build the scene where it belongs. That’s what this shoot was about. It’s not about visibility. It’s about memory. If you want the prompts I used to build this visual system — from motion blur to grain layering to rhythm logic — drop your favorite running scene in the comments. I’ll send one prompt back to someone. #PromptEngineering #AIContentDesign #RunningBrand #CreativeDirection #AIGeneratedVisuals #AIWorkflow #AIPhotoSystem #GenerativeDesign #BrandingWithAI #MotionAsMessage #VisualIdentity #NoProductJustFeeling #AIphotoeffects #SocialCampaignDesign #AIGraphicDesign

description: 🚨 New Shoe Alert - The Gel Nimbus 26 🚨 Last year when I was battling shin splints for months during my half marathon prep I made the switch over the Gel Nimbus 25 as the primary shoe for most of my miles. Asics did a complete overhaul of the shoe and turned the line into a max cushion shoe that is prefect for easy miles.  With summer coming up and more miles on the docket it was time to pick up a new pair for all of those base building miles that can make or break your race prep. The 26s were at the top of my list with small tweaks to the forefoot with a wider toe box (amazing for those of us who wear barefoot shoes outside of running) and a tread that will provide more grip to the ground.   The max cushioning does tend to slow you down, but thats a good thing for certain runs. I find that my pace picks up too much in snappier shoes like my Endorphin Speeds. Every runner needs a solid, boring, workhorse of a shoe in their rotation.  I was able to grab a colourway that I couldn’t find on the Asics website from Black Toe that keeps things simple and muted - leaving those bold colourways for race day and track sessions where they belong.  Fired up to log some serious miles in these shoes over the next month and I’ll report back with a full review then 🫡 #GelNimbus26 #MarathonTraining #EasyRuns #RunningGear #ShoeReview #RunningCommunity #RecoveryRun #RunningShoesUnboxing
